The reason I have come for a sight test today is because I broke my glasses during my archery lesson, and I think I'm due. Luckily, I can still see well without my glasses in the distance and near, but I know I need to wear my glasses all the time otherwise I'll get eyestrain and headaches, so I'd like new glasses as fast as possible.
 I believe my last sight test was just under 2 years ago, when I got my current glasses which are now broken. I could see clearly with my glasses, so I don't think my vision has changed much.
 I remember being told that my glasses help relax my eye muscles, so they don't overwork and strain trying to see clearly

 I haven't had any problems with my eyes like infections or surgery, and I've never been to the hospital to have my eyes checked either.
 There have been no eye problems in my family either as far as I'm aware.

 There have been no eye problems in my family either as far as I'm aware. Oh wait, my grandma had eye surgery recently to remove a cloudy lens from her eye.
 My family's general health is good, no-one in my direct family has high blood pressure or diabetes, we all take our health pretty seriously.
 My general health is very good; I don't have any problems at all.

 My general health is very good; I don't have any problems at all. I'm generally quite active and enjoy sports. I don't take any tables or medication. I don't smoke as I know it's damaging to my health.

 I spend about 7 hours a day looking at my computer and phone screen since I'm a student studying Nutrition at the University of Manchester. I'm pretty good at taking breaks though as I can't sit down for long periods of time!
 In my spare time I like to refine my archery skills at my club, but I do find my glasses sometimes come in my way.
